Justification Of Preliminary Recommendation:
FreshPER addresses a genuine failure mode in LLM RL with a theoretically motivated and practically simple solution, demonstrating meaningful performance gains on challenging agentic tasks. However, the paper has several issues that preclude acceptance in its current form: the core novelty claim cannot be verified without experimental comparison against RLEP and related concurrent work; the theoretical treatment of off-policy correction is inconsistent with the presented loss function; and the VLM contribution is limited to only two datasets, with GeoQA showing a negligible +1.3% improvement. We therefore recommend weak reject.

